Eva zu Beck....that was a tremendous accomplishment, particularly with temperatures of about 100 degrees Fahrenheit. I have done 25 marathons, and live in Las Vegas, and have run in Death Valley when it was 130, and did some long runs when it was around 100 degrees, but never beyond 14 or so miles. For it to be that hot for you after 20 miles, where you finished in good form was just astounding. If you ever want to go out to Death Valley in July, let me know, as running on the salt flats in a valley between mountain ranges of all kinds of coloration is quite an experience...especially when it is 120 degrees or better.  However, they have (or had) a marathon in December, and it was really nice. Eva zu Beck....you are stronger than you know you are. If you do some good long runs, and maybe run in cooler temps, you will be fast. Lots of good wishes for you.
